# Privacy Policy — Volume Booster

**Last updated:** 6 April 2026

## Overview

Volume Booster is a Chrome extension that allows users to boost the volume of video and audio elements on any webpage beyond the normal 100% limit. This privacy policy explains how the extension handles user data.

## Data Collection

Volume Booster does **not** collect, store, transmit, or share any user data. Specifically, the extension does not collect:

- Personal information (name, email, address, or any identifiers)
- Browsing history or web activity
- Authentication or financial information
- Location data
- Website content
- Usage analytics or telemetry

## How the Extension Works

The extension uses the Web Audio API to amplify media elements on the current page. All processing occurs locally within your browser. The extension makes no external network requests and communicates with no servers.

## Data Storage

The extension does not persist any data to disk. Volume settings are held in memory only and reset when the page is closed or refreshed.

## Third Parties

No user data is sold, transferred, or disclosed to any third party.

## Permissions

The extension requests host permissions (`<all_urls>`) solely to inject a content script that detects and boosts media elements on the active page. This permission is not used to read, collect, or transmit any page content or user data.

